<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1100,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1100,1125]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A genus of the family 
<taxonomicName box="[562,713,1100,1125]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Scorpaenidae</taxonomicName>
with the following combination of characters: body strongly compressed, body width 
<number box="[446,518,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="17.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="10.0">10–24</number>
% of 
<collectionCode box="[588,623,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">SL</collectionCode>
, and elongated, body depth 
<number box="[963,1035,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="34.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="28.0">28–40</number>
% of 
<collectionCode box="[1104,1140,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">SL</collectionCode>
; 
<number box="[1157,1185,1136,1160]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="12.0">12</number>
dorsal-fin spines; no palatine teeth; tympanic spines present; upper posttemporal spines absent; body scales cycloid; lower pectoral-fin rays not strongly notched, not filamentous; no black blotches on lower caudal fin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="491" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1100,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1244,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Remarks.</emphasis>
The scorpionfish genera, 
<taxonomicName box="[612,774,1244,1269]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[612,774,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[789,1131,1244,1269]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Hipposcorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[789,976,1245,1268]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Hipposcorpaena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fowler" box="[984,1131,1244,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Fowler, H. W. (1938) Descriptions of new fishes obtained by the United States Bureau of Fisheries steamer &quot; Albatross &quot;, chiefly in Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 85 (3032), 31 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.85 - 3032.31" type="journal article" year="1938">
Fowler 
<number box="[1072,1131,1244,1268]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1938.0">1938</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill, 1905" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1905" box="[1192,1432,1244,1269]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Rhinopias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1306,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Rhinopias</emphasis>
Gill, 
<number box="[1373,1432,1244,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1905.0">1905</number>
</taxonomicName>
, are closely related to each other (
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" box="[519,819,1279,1304]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Senou, H. (2005) Validity of the scorpionfish genus Hipposcorpaena Fowler and a redescription of H. filamentosa Fowler (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Zoological Studies, 44, 210 - 218." type="journal article" year="2005">
Motomura &amp; Senou, 
<number box="[759,819,1279,1304]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" box="[830,1150,1279,1304]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Johnson, J. W. (2006) Validity of the poorly known scorpionfish, Rhinopias eschmeyeri, with redescriptions of R. frondosa and R. aphanes (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Copeia, 2006, 500 - 515. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1643 / 0045 - 8511 (2006) 2006 [500: VOTPKS] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Motomura &amp; Johnson, 
<number box="[1089,1150,1279,1304]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authority="Regan, 1908" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1908" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pogonoscorpius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1351,1281,1304]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pogonoscorpius</emphasis>
Regan, 
<number box="[151,207,1316,1340]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[490,603,1316,1341]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Rhinopias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,603,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Rhinopias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Motomura unpub. data). These genera are distinguished from all other genera of the family 
<taxonomicName box="[381,532,1351,1376]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Scorpaenidae</taxonomicName>
by having 
<number box="[655,683,1352,1376]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="12.0">12</number>
dorsal-fin spines, a strongly compressed body, cycloid body scales, and no teeth on the palatines (
<bibRefCitation author="Poss" box="[492,745,1388,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Poss, S. G. (1999) Scorpaenidae. Scorpionfishes (also, lionfishes, rockfishes, stingfishes, stonefishes, and waspfishes). In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), FAO species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the western central Pacific. Vol. 4. Bony fishes part 2, Mugilidae to Carangidae. FAO, Rome, pp. 2291 - 2352." type="journal article" year="1999">
Poss, 
<number box="[560,619,1388,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1999.0">1999</number>
; this study
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[765,927,1388,1413]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[765,927,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1266,1389,1412]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Hipposcorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1079,1266,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Hipposcorpaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1436,1388,1413]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Rhinopias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1436,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Rhinopias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a shallower body depth [
<number box="[540,614,1424,1448]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="34.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="28.0">28–40</number>
% of 
<collectionCode box="[675,708,1424,1448]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">SL</collectionCode>
vs. 
<number box="[755,826,1423,1448]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="46.5" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="40.0">40–53</number>
% of 
<collectionCode box="[886,919,1424,1448]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">SL</collectionCode>
in the latter two genera, data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Senou, H. (2005) Validity of the scorpionfish genus Hipposcorpaena Fowler and a redescription of H. filamentosa Fowler (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Zoological Studies, 44, 210 - 218." type="journal article" year="2005">
Motomura &amp; Senou (
<number box="[265,324,1460,1485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" box="[386,717,1460,1485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Johnson, J. W. (2006) Validity of the poorly known scorpionfish, Rhinopias eschmeyeri, with redescriptions of R. frondosa and R. aphanes (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Copeia, 2006, 500 - 515. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1643 / 0045 - 8511 (2006) 2006 [500: VOTPKS] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Motomura &amp; Johnson (
<number box="[648,710,1460,1485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<number box="[729,801,1460,1485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="46.0" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="38.0">38–54</number>
% of 
<collectionCode box="[860,893,1460,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">SL</collectionCode>
from 
<bibRefCitation author="Poss" box="[962,1100,1460,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Poss, S. G. (1999) Scorpaenidae. Scorpionfishes (also, lionfishes, rockfishes, stingfishes, stonefishes, and waspfishes). In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), FAO species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the western central Pacific. Vol. 4. Bony fishes part 2, Mugilidae to Carangidae. FAO, Rome, pp. 2291 - 2352." type="journal article" year="1999">
Poss (
<number box="[1029,1091,1460,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
], tympanic spines present (vs. spines absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[342,456,1495,1520]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Rhinopias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[342,456,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Rhinopias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the lower pectoral-fin rays not strongly notched (vs. strongly notched, forming filaments in 
<taxonomicName box="[292,479,1533,1556]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Hipposcorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,479,1533,1556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Hipposcorpaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and in lacking upper posttemporal spines (spines present in 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1289,1532,1557]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Rhinopias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1175,1289,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Rhinopias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and lacking black blotches on the lower caudal fin (
<number box="[613,656,1568,1592]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
distinct blotches present in 
<taxonomicName box="[984,1171,1569,1592]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Hipposcorpaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[984,1171,1569,1592]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Hipposcorpaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Senou, H. (2005) Validity of the scorpionfish genus Hipposcorpaena Fowler and a redescription of H. filamentosa Fowler (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Zoological Studies, 44, 210 - 218." type="journal article" year="2005">
Motomura &amp; Senou, 
<number box="[151,211,1604,1629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Motomura" box="[221,542,1604,1629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H. &amp; Johnson, J. W. (2006) Validity of the poorly known scorpionfish, Rhinopias eschmeyeri, with redescriptions of R. frondosa and R. aphanes (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenidae). Copeia, 2006, 500 - 515. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1643 / 0045 - 8511 (2006) 2006 [500: VOTPKS] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">
Motomura &amp; Johnson, 
<number box="[481,542,1604,1629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1100,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[327,447,1639,1664]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,447,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteropelor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fowler" box="[784,948,1639,1664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Fowler, H. W. (1938) Descriptions of new fishes obtained by the United States Bureau of Fisheries steamer &quot; Albatross &quot;, chiefly in Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 85 (3032), 31 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.85 - 3032.31" type="journal article" year="1938">
Fowler (
<number box="[882,940,1640,1664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for his new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1197,1428,1639,1664]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noronhai">
<emphasis box="[1197,1428,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteropelor noronhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from off 
<collectingCountry box="[251,385,1677,1701]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[396,466,1676,1701]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">China</collectingCountry>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[590,805,1676,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Chen, L. - C. &amp; Liu, W. - Y. (1984) Pteroidichthys amboinensis, a scorpaenid fish new to Taiwan, with a description of the species and a discussion of its validity. Journal of Taiwan Museum, 37, 101 - 103." type="journal article" year="1984">
Chen &amp; Liu (
<number box="[738,796,1676,1700]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mandrytsa" box="[859,1054,1676,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Mandrytsa, S. A. (2001) Lateral line system and classification of scorpaenoid fishes (Scorpaeniformes: Scorpaenoidei). Perm University Press, Perm, 393 pp." type="book" year="2001">Mandrytsa (2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mandrytsa" box="[1065,1123,1676,1700]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Mandrytsa, S. A. (2002) New records of rare scorpaenids fishes from the genera Pteropelor and Rhinopias (Scorpaenidae) in the Indian and western Pacific Oceans. Journal of Ichthyology, 42, 544 - 547." type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
) treated it as a valid species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Poss (1999)" authorityName="Poss" authorityYear="1999" box="[182,451,1711,1736]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,301,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteropelor</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poss" box="[317,451,1712,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Poss, S. G. (1999) Scorpaenidae. Scorpionfishes (also, lionfishes, rockfishes, stingfishes, stonefishes, and waspfishes). In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), FAO species identification guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the western central Pacific. Vol. 4. Bony fishes part 2, Mugilidae to Carangidae. FAO, Rome, pp. 2291 - 2352." type="journal article" year="1999">
Poss (
<number box="[384,442,1712,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[508,786,1711,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Motomura, H., Bearez, P. &amp; Causse, R. (2011 a) Review of Indo-Pacific specimens of the subfamily Scorpaeninae (Scorpaenidae), deposited in the Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, with description of a new species of Neomerinthe. Cybium, 35, 55 - 73." type="journal article">
Motomura 
<emphasis box="[634,684,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[707,765,1712,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
regarded it as a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1258,1711,1736]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1096,1258,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fowler" box="[1274,1436,1711,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" refString="Fowler, H. W. (1938) Descriptions of new fishes obtained by the United States Bureau of Fisheries steamer &quot; Albatross &quot;, chiefly in Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 85 (3032), 31 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.85 - 3032.31" type="journal article" year="1938">
Fowler (
<number box="[1369,1427,1712,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[274,394,1748,1773]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,394,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteropelor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[544,706,1748,1773]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[544,706,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in “its incised spinous dorsal membranes, absence of barbels, and large scales”. However, these general characters usually represent species-level differences in the family 
<taxonomicName box="[233,388,1820,1845]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Scorpaenidae</taxonomicName>
. In addition, differences in the number of anal-fin spines (
<number box="[1062,1077,1820,1844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="2.0">2</number>
vs. 
<number box="[1127,1141,1820,1844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="3.0">3</number>
) and the condition of the dorsal-fin spines (flexible vs. rigid) found between 
<taxonomicName box="[754,926,1855,1880]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis box="[754,926,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">P. amboinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[988,1120,1855,1880]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noronhai">
<emphasis box="[988,1120,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">P. noronhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be thought equal to generic features, but characters of a newly described species in this study, 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1130,1893,1916]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caussei">
<emphasis box="[1017,1130,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">P. caussei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, represent an intermediate condition between the two species, 
<emphasis box="[562,589,1929,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">i.e</emphasis>
., having 
<number box="[698,712,1928,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" value="3.0">3</number>
anal-fin spines and rigid dorsal-fin spines. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[1287,1407,1927,1952]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1407,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteropelor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herein regarded as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[657,819,1964,1989]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,819,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[898,1035,1964,1989]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteropelor" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noronhai">
<emphasis box="[898,1035,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">P. noronhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated as a valid species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,313,2000,2025]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scorpaenidae" genus="Pteroidichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,313,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="491">Pteroidichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
